name: Pounded yam
description: Yams that have been crushed or stirred to a creamy, dough - like consistency.Pounded yams are considered a fufu(a kind of starchy side dish) usually served with a stew or efo.

name: Jollof rice
description: Rice made with tomatoes, onions, scotch bonnets, and chili peppers. There are endless variations on this recipe, but those five ingredients are usual constants.

name: Egusi Soup
description: A stew usually made with crayfish or other meat and thickened with ground melon seeds(egusi).

name: Pepper Soup
description: Light and spicy soup traditionally made with goat meat, but often with fish or other meat, as well as herbs and Nigerian spices.

name: Efo Riro
description: A rich spinach stew usually made with spinach, scotch bonnets, and red bell peppers.

description: Fried bean cakes.Usually served as a breakfast food or snack and made with black eyed peas, these fritters are crunchy, spicy, and perfect alone or with a dipping sauce.

description: Deep fried plantain slices.

name: Puff puff
description: Deep fried dough, served plain or with powdered sugar.

description: Yams that have been crushed or stirred to a creamy, dough - like consistency.Pounded yams are considered a fufu(a kind of starchy side dish) usually served with a stew or efo.
